00:23:46,288 --> 00:23:48,189
Thank you.

454
00:23:48,209 --> 00:23:52,991
I noticed that in some of your examples, you used a game pad for controlling the...

455
00:23:53,978 --> 00:23:55,979
the game and in some of them it was gestures.

456
00:23:56,499 --> 00:24:00,261
What do you think are the unique challenges

457
00:24:00,681 --> 00:24:02,562
as far as control space between,

458
00:24:02,862 --> 00:24:04,743
like the differences between those?

459
00:24:04,823 --> 00:24:05,504
That's a good question.

460
00:24:05,624 --> 00:24:07,385
You know, challenges with regards to control.

461
00:24:07,505 --> 00:24:10,306
I think what I've noticed when people first use

462
00:24:10,326 --> 00:24:12,047
these devices is they start reaching out at stuff.

463
00:24:12,527 --> 00:24:14,988
So obviously having hand gestures is super, super important.

464
00:24:15,569 --> 00:24:18,390
Now, the problem is though, I feel that once you get

465
00:24:18,430 --> 00:24:21,091
beyond that initial stage, you always have to have that

466
00:24:21,111 --> 00:24:21,692
to be intuitive.

467
00:24:22,807 --> 00:24:25,408
I feel that beyond that though, hands are not very intuitive.

468
00:24:25,528 --> 00:24:27,989
And in fact, if you think about what hands are used for,

469
00:24:28,009 --> 00:24:29,429
they're used for manipulating tools,

470
00:24:30,249 --> 00:24:31,589
not like pointing and waving at things.

471
00:24:31,969 --> 00:24:33,970
And I think that people that are very zealous

472
00:24:34,010 --> 00:24:36,310
about using only hand gestures are missing a key part

473
00:24:36,350 --> 00:24:38,311
of the human anatomy and why we have hands.

474
00:24:39,311 --> 00:24:40,871
The Xbox 360 controller, I think,

475
00:24:40,951 --> 00:24:42,372
is unfortunately not something Microsoft

476
00:24:42,412 --> 00:24:44,472
is gonna move forward with in terms of a control device,

477
00:24:44,512 --> 00:24:46,013
but I find it to be extremely useful.

478
00:24:46,273 --> 00:24:48,513
I personally prefer it to motion controller type controls.

479
00:24:49,033 --> 00:24:50,554
I think a combination of something like that

480
00:24:50,754 --> 00:24:52,174
and hand controls would be great.

481
00:24:53,855 --> 00:24:56,717
But if you really want fine, persistent control,

482
00:24:56,737 --> 00:24:58,458
when you're trying to design something, for example,

483
00:24:59,179 --> 00:25:01,180
something like a controller actually works really well.

484
00:25:01,860 --> 00:25:03,762
And I like the fact that it's one single thing,

485
00:25:03,782 --> 00:25:06,483
so I can take one hand away and start waving around,

486
00:25:06,663 --> 00:25:08,505
potentially, and then return to my controller.

487
00:25:09,605 --> 00:25:11,567
So I think realistically, though,

488
00:25:11,587 --> 00:25:13,608
it's gonna be a combination of just intuitive hand controls

489
00:25:13,808 --> 00:25:15,869
as much as possible, picking up voice,

490
